definitions.definition: A seal , as of a letter.
A special characteristic or quality ; prestige , especially via association .
examples: I remember when this diner was a quiet hangout, but lately it seems to be losing its cachet .

definitions.definition: A commemorative stamped design or inscription on an envelope, other than a cancellation or pre-printed postage.
A sealed envelope containing an item whose price is being negotiated.
A capsule containing a pharmaceutical preparation.
A hidden location from which one can observe birds while remaining unseen.

main_definition: ( archaic ) A seal , as of a letter.
secondary_definitions: ( figurative ) A special characteristic or quality ; prestige , especially via association .
( philately ) A commemorative stamped design or inscription on an envelope, other than a cancellation or pre-printed postage.
A sealed envelope containing an item whose price is being negotiated.
( medicine ) A capsule containing a pharmaceutical preparation.
A hidden location from which one can observe birds while remaining unseen.
